&lt;pre&gt;On Wed, Jul 23, 2025 at 2:39 PM Zainab Rizvi &lt;riz...@google.com&gt; wrote:&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

&gt; My appologies, Yoav. I had a draft response that hadn't sent.
&gt;
&gt; We have documented an appeals process
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://privacysandbox.google.com/protections/masked-domain-list/appeals#:~:text=Domain%20owners%20can%20expect%20the,from%20the%20initial%20appeal%20request"&gt;https://privacysandbox.google.com/protections/masked-domain-list/appeals#:~:text=Domain%20owners%20can%20expect%20the,from%20the%20initial%20appeal%20request&lt;/a&gt;.&gt;
&gt;  that
&gt; can be used by domain owners to request evidence for their inclusion on the
&gt; list. This evidence would include examples of URLs that will be blocked, as
&gt; well as top-level sites where they are embedded. If the domain does not
&gt; meet the MDL inclusion criteria, it will be removed within a defined SLA.
&gt; We are already seeing some domain owners use the appeals process.
&gt;

Thanks! That process is not very clear for the &quot;Some URLs are blocked&quot; case.
For example, how can Google appeal the inclusion of &quot;storage.googleapis.com&quot;
in that list when it doesn't know which URLs are being blocked, and
therefore doesn't know if these URLs meet the MDL inclusion criteria?


&gt;
&gt; On Friday, June 20, 2025 at 11:58:47 AM UTC-4 yoav...@chromium.org wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt; On Fri, Jun 20, 2025 at 5:21 PM Zainab Rizvi &lt;riz...@google.com&gt; wrote:
