&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Rollout plan Will ship enabled for all users
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Requires code in //chrome? False
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Tracking bug &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues/377278827"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues/377278827&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Measurement Browser bound keys are an additive to Secure Payment
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Confirmation: The Secure Payment Confirmation UseCounter will be used.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Availability expectation Secure Payment Confirmation (and Browser
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Bound Keys) are only in Chromium browsers for the foreseeable future.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Non-OSS dependencies
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Does the feature depend on any code or APIs outside the Chromium open
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; source repository and its open-source dependencies to function?
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; No
